Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.92,English,,0,0,0,,Most people don't know how bicycles actually work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们大多不清楚  自行车是如何保持稳定的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:04.64,English,,0,0,0,,- Let's try it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:04.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-我们再试一次
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.64,0:00:07.61,English,,0,0,0,,So we modified this bike to prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.64,0:00:07.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我们改装出这辆自行车来证实它
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.85,0:00:14.10,English,,0,0,0,,This video was sponsored by KiwiCo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.85,0:00:14.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,（广告不翻译）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.10,0:00:16.05,English,,0,0,0,,More about them at the end of the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.10,0:00:16.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,（广告不翻译）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.63,0:00:20.12,English,,0,0,0,,- When you're riding a bike and you want to turn left,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.63,0:00:20.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当你在骑行时  如果你想左转
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.12,0:00:21.61,English,,0,0,0,,I think most people just imagine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.12,0:00:21.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我猜大多数人都以为
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.61,0:00:23.84,English,,0,0,0,,you turn the handlebars to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.61,0:00:23.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将车把向左转就可以了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.84,0:00:26.49,English,,0,0,0,,This is a bike to test whether that is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.84,0:00:26.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们要用这辆单车  来检验这一想法是否正确
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.49,0:00:29.02,English,,0,0,0,,And it's made by my friend Rick here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.49,0:00:29.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是由我的朋友Rick制作的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.02,0:00:30.80,English,,0,0,0,,and he's got a radio controller that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.02,0:00:30.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他手里拿的这个遥控器
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:35.04,English,,0,0,0,,allows him to lock out the steering to one side.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:35.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以锁住车把只能朝一个方向转
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.04,0:00:36.73,English,,0,0,0,,So, what he's gonna do is as I'm biking,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.04,0:00:36.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我骑这辆车的时候 Rick要做的是
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.73,0:00:38.90,English,,0,0,0,,he's gonna pick whether I can turn
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.73,0:00:38.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,决定我可以往哪儿转
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.90,0:00:40.67,English,,0,0,0,,either to the left or to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.90,0:00:40.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是往左转  还是往右转
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.67,0:00:42.21,English,,0,0,0,,So, go for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.67,0:00:42.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开始吧
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:43.80,English,,0,0,0,,- I'm giving it a left turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.21,0:00:43.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-现在我给他一个可以左转的命令
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.80,0:00:45.14,English,,0,0,0,,It pulls the pin out,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.80,0:00:45.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,栓被拉出
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.14,0:00:48.20,English,,0,0,0,,but you can see that you can still fully steer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.14,0:00:48.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但你现在仍可以随意转动车把
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.20,0:00:49.08,English,,0,0,0,,after I've pulled the pin out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.20,0:00:49.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我将栓完全拉出
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.08,0:00:50.47,English,,0,0,0,,I've armed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.08,0:00:50.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我打开了它的保险
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:52.39,English,,0,0,0,,There's where it locks. - OK
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:52.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就意味着它锁上了  -好的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.39,0:00:55.11,English,,0,0,0,,Now, that that's when your LED comes on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.39,0:00:55.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在LED亮了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.11,0:00:56.38,English,,0,0,0,,and that just says turn that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.11,0:00:56.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,意味着朝这个方向转弯
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.38,0:00:57.65,English,,0,0,0,,- Turn left. - Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.38,0:00:57.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-左转  -没错
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.65,0:01:00.07,English,,0,0,0,,And if I try to turn right, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.65,0:01:00.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我尝试右转的话 我做不到
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.07,0:01:01.28,English,,0,0,0,,And if I try to turn left-
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.07,0:01:01.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我尝试左转的话
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:02.11,English,,0,0,0,,- You can.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:02.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-你可以
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.11,0:01:02.94,English,,0,0,0,,- I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.11,0:01:02.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-我可以
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.94,0:01:03.92,English,,0,0,0,,So the question is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.94,0:01:03.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,问题在于
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.92,0:01:07.43,English,,0,0,0,,can I successfully execute this left-hand turn?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.92,0:01:07.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我能否成功地执行左转的命令
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.43,0:01:08.26,English,,0,0,0,,Should we give it a shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.43,0:01:08.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们要试试吗
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.26,0:01:09.91,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, he's not gonna tell me whether it's left or right,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.26,0:01:09.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Rick不会直接告诉我左转还是右转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.91,0:01:11.71,English,,0,0,0,,so I have to look at the LED to know
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.91,0:01:11.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我只能通过看灯来确认
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.71,0:01:13.77,English,,0,0,0,,which way I can still turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.71,0:01:13.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我可以朝哪个方向转弯
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.77,0:01:15.42,English,,0,0,0,,- You let me know when you're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.77,0:01:15.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-你准备好了示意我
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.88,0:01:17.71,English,,0,0,0,,- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.88,0:01:17.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.25,0:01:22.17,English,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.25,0:01:22.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.17,0:01:23.75,English,,0,0,0,,That was meant to be a turn to the right
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.17,0:01:23.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,刚才那应该是一个右转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.75,0:01:25.50,English,,0,0,0,,but there was no chance in hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.75,0:01:25.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但没有机会了
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.50,0:01:26.55,English,,0,0,0,,Left.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.50,0:01:26.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,左转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.83,0:01:28.66,English,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.83,0:01:28.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,右转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.30,0:01:33.18,English,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.30,0:01:33.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好吧
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.46,0:01:37.58,English,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.46,0:01:37.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,右转 右转 右转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.58,0:01:39.10,English,,0,0,0,,God!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.58,0:01:39.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,淦
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.10,0:01:41.90,English,,0,0,0,,- If you look closely, you can see the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.10,0:01:41.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仔细看的话可以发现问题所在
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.90,0:01:44.15,English,,0,0,0,,Here, I'm trying to turn right
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.90,0:01:44.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我现在打算右转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:47.93,English,,0,0,0,,but steering that way puts me off balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.15,0:01:47.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但把车头往右转过去  会让我失去平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.93,0:01:49.69,English,,0,0,0,,If you could ride this bicycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.93,0:01:49.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当你骑上这辆车时
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.69,0:01:51.95,English,,0,0,0,,you would find it's impossible to turn left
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.69,0:01:51.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就会发现  要想左转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.95,0:01:53.68,English,,0,0,0,,without first steering right
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.95,0:01:53.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就不得不先往右摆
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.68,0:01:55.24,English,,0,0,0,,and it's impossible to turn right
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.68,0:01:55.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同样  如果想右转
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.24,0:01:57.56,English,,0,0,0,,without first steering left.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.24,0:01:57.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就一定要先往左摆
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.41,0:02:00.41,English,,0,0,0,,This seems wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.41,0:02:00.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这看起来很离谱
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.41,0:02:02.00,English,,0,0,0,,I think most people believe you turn a bike
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.41,0:02:02.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我想  大多数人都相信转弯时
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.00,0:02:03.79,English,,0,0,0,,simply by pointing the handlebars
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.00,0:02:03.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只需要简单的将把手
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.79,0:02:05.50,English,,0,0,0,,in the direction you want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.79,0:02:05.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转到想要前进的方向就可以
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.50,0:02:08.55,English,,0,0,0,,After all, this is how you drive a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.50,0:02:08.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟 我们是这样开车的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.55,0:02:10.95,English,,0,0,0,,Point the front wheels any direction you like
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.55,0:02:10.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将前轮朝向任何你想前进的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.95,0:02:13.35,English,,0,0,0,,and the car just goes that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.95,0:02:13.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,车就会朝那个方向行驶
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.35,0:02:14.82,English,,0,0,0,,But the difference with a bicycle
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.35,0:02:14.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而自行车与之不同
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.82,0:02:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,is steering doesn't just affect the direction you're headed;
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.82,0:02:18.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不能做到车把朝哪转 车就往哪拐
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.50,0:02:21.69,English,,0,0,0,,it also affects your balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.50,0:02:21.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转动车把也会影响你的平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.69,0:02:24.03,English,,0,0,0,,Imagine you want to make a right turn
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.69,0:02:24.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,想象一下你要右转弯
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.03,0:02:26.60,English,,0,0,0,,so you steer the handlebars to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.03,0:02:26.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以你将车把朝右转
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.60,0:02:28.63,English,,0,0,0,,What you've done is effectively
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.63,0:02:31.18,English,,0,0,0,,steered the bike out from under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.60,0:02:31.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样做会立即使你失去平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.18,0:02:33.86,English,,0,0,0,,So now you're leaning to the left
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.18,0:02:33.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以你现在朝左倾斜
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.86,0:02:36.20,English,,0,0,0,,and the ground puts a force on the bike to the left
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.86,0:02:36.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,同时地面会给车子向左的支撑力
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.20,0:02:38.04,English,,0,0,0,,so the only way not to fall
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.20,0:02:38.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,避免摔倒的唯一方式
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.04,0:02:40.31,English,,0,0,0,,is to steer the bike to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.04,0:02:40.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是向左转
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.31,0:02:42.86,English,,0,0,0,,You have made a left turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.31,0:02:42.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你完成了一次左转
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.86,0:02:44.81,English,,0,0,0,,If you really wanted to turn right,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.86,0:02:44.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你真的要右转
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:47.31,English,,0,0,0,,you first have to counter-steer to the left
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.81,0:02:47.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你反而先要左转
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.31,0:02:50.89,English,,0,0,0,,so you can lean right into the turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.31,0:02:50.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,才可以向右倾斜  从而完成右转
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:54.32,English,,0,0,0,,This is something anyone who rides a bike knows intuitively
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:54.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所有人在骑车时都会靠直觉做到这点
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:55.97,English,,0,0,0,,but not explicitly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.32,0:02:55.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但自己意识不到
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:02:57.25,English,,0,0,0,,- Turn left!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:02:57.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-左转
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.25,0:02:59.43,English,,0,0,0,,- Film someone riding a bike towards you and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.25,0:02:59.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-拍摄他人朝你骑行的镜头
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:01.29,English,,0,0,0,,tell them which direction to turn
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:01.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并告诉他们朝哪个方向转向
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.29,0:03:02.11,English,,0,0,0,,and you will find that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.29,0:03:02.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就会发现
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.11,0:03:04.57,English,,0,0,0,,they counter-steer without even thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.11,0:03:04.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们不假思索地就会先将车把朝反方向转
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.57,0:03:05.78,English,,0,0,0,,- Hard left!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.57,0:03:05.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-向左急转弯
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.97,0:03:10.64,English,,0,0,0,,When you're riding a bike,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.97,0:03:10.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你骑单车的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.64,0:03:13.46,English,,0,0,0,,it's exactly the same as what we call an inverted pendulum
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.64,0:03:13.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其原理完全符合我们所说的“倒单摆”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:16.20,English,,0,0,0,,or balancing a broomstick on your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.46,0:03:16.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也就是在手面上倒立扫帚
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.20,0:03:18.77,English,,0,0,0,,If I'm balancing it and I just start walking toward you,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.20,0:03:18.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我平衡好之后  如果我开始朝你走去
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.77,0:03:21.15,English,,0,0,0,,it will always fall away from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.77,0:03:21.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,扫帚反而会倒向我
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,If I want to walk towards you, it's easy enough to do
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:23.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我想朝你走去  正确做法不难
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.02,0:03:24.72,English,,0,0,0,,and people inherently know how to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.02,0:03:24.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,人们天生、无意识地就能做到
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.72,0:03:28.40,English,,0,0,0,,If I pull it backward, I can now start walking that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.72,0:03:28.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我先往后拉  就能开始往前走了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.40,0:03:32.71,English,,0,0,0,,I have to initiate the lean to turn into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.40,0:03:32.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我先要制造前倾  才能在向前走的时候动态保持住
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.71,0:03:34.66,English,,0,0,0,,- If you want to move the pendulum somewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.71,0:03:34.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你想把倒单摆往某个方向移动
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.66,0:03:37.97,English,,0,0,0,,you first move the base in the opposite direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.66,0:03:37.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就先得把底下的支点  往相反方向移动
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.97,0:03:39.96,English,,0,0,0,,And now the pendulum is leaning
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.96,0:03:41.43,English,,0,0,0,,in the direction you want to go
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.97,0:03:41.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,倒单摆朝你想去的方向倾斜了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.43,0:03:44.35,English,,0,0,0,,so you can move with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.43,0:03:44.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就能朝着这个方向走了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.35,0:03:47.10,English,,0,0,0,,And it's the same with a unicycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.35,0:03:47.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,独轮车的原理类似
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.10,0:03:48.51,English,,0,0,0,,In order to go forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.10,0:03:48.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你要想往前走
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:50.26,English,,0,0,0,,first, you have to peddle back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.51,0:03:50.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就要先把踏板往回踩
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.26,0:03:52.03,English,,0,0,0,,So, you're leaning forward
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.26,0:03:52.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是  你的重心往前倾斜
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.03,0:03:54.71,English,,0,0,0,,and then you can go forward with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.03,0:03:54.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你才能向前移动
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:56.27,English,,0,0,0,,- Everything you're doing on a unicycle
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.71,0:03:56.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你在做独轮车上做的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.27,0:03:59.12,English,,0,0,0,,is all about keeping that contact patch
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.27,0:03:59.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都是要把轮胎与地面的接触面
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:01.71,English,,0,0,0,,right where it needs to be relative to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.12,0:04:01.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,维持在你想去的方向的前面
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.71,0:04:03.38,English,,0,0,0,,You're balancing the broomstick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.71,0:04:03.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,跟立扫帚差不多
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.38,0:04:04.86,English,,0,0,0,,It's just that on a unicycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.38,0:04:04.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只不过在独轮车上
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.86,0:04:08.22,English,,0,0,0,,you do the longitudinal balance with the pedals
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.86,0:04:08.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你要维持纵向的平衡  需要借助踏板
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.22,0:04:10.81,English,,0,0,0,,and you do the lateral balance, the side to side,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.22,0:04:10.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而维持侧向的平衡时
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:11.72,English,,0,0,0,,the same as you do with a bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.81,0:04:11.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就跟骑单车一样了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.72,0:04:14.65,English,,0,0,0,,You essentially- sorta, small counter-steer to get that weight,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.72,0:04:14.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你也是先要略往反方向转  让重心往正确的方向移动
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:16.66,English,,0,0,0,,to get the contact patch out,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.65,0:04:16.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让接触面移过去
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.66,0:04:19.35,English,,0,0,0,,and then you can pedal and bring it under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.66,0:04:19.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你才能踩踏板带着它走
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:20.39,English,,0,0,0,,- Now I should point out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:20.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我得指出一点
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.39,0:04:22.57,English,,0,0,0,,that sometimes when the steering locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.39,0:04:22.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转向装置被锁住的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.57,0:04:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,we just happened to be leaning in the right direction
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.57,0:04:25.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我的重心可能正好倾斜向右
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.14,0:04:26.85,English,,0,0,0,,to execute the turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.14,0:04:26.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,于是我就能完成转向了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.39,0:04:30.54,English,,0,0,0,,- Oh, managed it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.39,0:04:30.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,喔  成了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:31.95,English,,0,0,0,,- Essentially by sheer luck,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.54,0:04:31.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只要比较欧皇
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.95,0:04:33.20,English,,0,0,0,,we had counter-steered
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.20,0:04:36.04,English,,0,0,0,,before that side of the handlebars locked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.95,0:04:36.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在把手锁住某一边时  重心刚调过去
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.04,0:04:37.76,English,,0,0,0,,Now, I can keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.04,0:04:37.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我就可以不摔下来
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:38.83,English,,0,0,0,,- [Rick] Yeah, but don't turn left
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:38.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但别转左喔
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:39.99,English,,0,0,0,,or you're gonna be screwed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:39.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不然你会——的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.99,0:04:42.02,English,,0,0,0,,- I can't turn left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.99,0:04:42.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我没法转左
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.02,0:04:43.29,English,,0,0,0,,What's interesting about this is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.02,0:04:43.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有意思的地方在于
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.29,0:04:45.97,English,,0,0,0,,it shows that you can still ride the bike perfectly well, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.29,0:04:45.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样的自行车  居然也能骑得稳当
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.97,0:04:48.73,English,,0,0,0,,It's just you can't turn left.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.97,0:04:48.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只是没法转左
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:52.21,English,,0,0,0,,The funny thing is that you couldn't initiate the turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.73,0:04:52.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好玩的是  你自己是没法转弯的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.21,0:04:54.70,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, the wild takeaway is that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.21,0:04:54.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.70,0:04:57.68,English,,0,0,0,,steering is not just for turning the bike;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.70,0:04:57.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转向装置不只是用来转弯的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.68,0:04:58.89,English,,0,0,0,,steering is for balancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.68,0:04:58.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还是用来维持平衡的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:00.25,English,,0,0,0,,- That's exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:00.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一点儿没错
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.25,0:05:03.82,English,,0,0,0,,- Why is it hard to balance on a stationary bike?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.25,0:05:03.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么我们难以定在静止的自行车上
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:04.83,English,,0,0,0,,I think most people believe
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:04.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我猜大多数人会以为
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.83,0:05:06.69,English,,0,0,0,,it's because the wheels aren't spinning
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.83,0:05:06.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是因为轮子不转
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.69,0:05:09.06,English,,0,0,0,,so there's no gyroscopic effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.69,0:05:09.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因而没有陀螺仪效应
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.06,0:05:10.89,English,,0,0,0,,but that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.06,0:05:10.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实并非如此
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.89,0:05:12.76,English,,0,0,0,,The truth is you use steering
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.89,0:05:12.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上  你是在用转向装置
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.76,0:05:14.83,English,,0,0,0,,to keep the bike underneath you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.76,0:05:14.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来稳住胯下的自行车
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:17.82,English,,0,0,0,,but steering doesn't work when you're stationary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:17.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但转向装置在车子静止时  无法起稳定作用
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.82,0:05:19.14,English,,0,0,0,,Your balance comes not so much
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.82,0:05:19.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自行车保持平衡的关键
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.14,0:05:21.61,English,,0,0,0,,from how you position your body over the bike,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.14,0:05:21.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是你怎样把身体在自行车上面稳住
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.61,0:05:25.27,English,,0,0,0,,but by how you steer the bike to keep it underneath you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.61,0:05:25.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是你怎样控制自行车  让它一直在你的下方
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.27,0:05:26.62,English,,0,0,0,,Even when going straight,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.27,0:05:26.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即使是向前直线行驶
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.62,0:05:29.33,English,,0,0,0,,you're constantly making small steering adjustments
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.62,0:05:29.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你也在不断对车头方向  进行微小的调整
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.33,0:05:31.20,English,,0,0,0,,to maintain balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.33,0:05:31.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来维持平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.20,0:05:32.65,English,,0,0,0,,- You're moving the contact patch
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.65,0:05:33.77,English,,0,0,0,,of the front wheel under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.20,0:05:33.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你要把前轮的接触面移到你下方
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.77,0:05:34.81,English,,0,0,0,,You're doing exactly what you do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.81,0:05:36.96,English,,0,0,0,,when you balance a broomstick on your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.77,0:05:36.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这跟你平衡手里的扫帚  是一个道理
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.99,0:05:39.84,English,,0,0,0,,- So, if the rider is responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:41.89,English,,0,0,0,,for steering the bike to keep it balanced,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.99,0:05:41.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,既然骑手得控制自行车、维持其平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:45.21,English,,0,0,0,,how do bikes without riders stay upright?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.89,0:05:45.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么自行车没了骑手  还能“自行”呢
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.21,0:05:47.74,English,,0,0,0,,As long as a bike is moving with sufficient speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.21,0:05:47.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只要自行车跑得够快
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:50.55,English,,0,0,0,,it can keep coasting indefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.74,0:05:50.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它就能沿着坡一直滑行下去
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.55,0:05:52.56,English,,0,0,0,,I first became aware of this phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.55,0:05:52.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我第一次留意这个现象
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:54.61,English,,0,0,0,,through the great videos by MinutePhysics,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:54.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是在“分钟物理”的视频里  整挺好
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:56.65,English,,0,0,0,,which inspired me to make this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:56.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这也是我做这个视频的灵感来源
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.65,0:05:58.75,English,,0,0,0,,You should definitely check them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.65,0:05:58.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你值得去看看
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:58.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an7\fs36}【分钟物理】自行车是怎么保持平衡的[中英字幕] \N靛蓝字幕组\NBV13s411m7C6
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:00.21,English,,0,0,0,,But it turned out the ground where we went to test this effect
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:00.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是  我们测试这个效应的场地
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:03.60,English,,0,0,0,,was really bumpy,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:03.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实在是太颠簸了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.60,0:06:06.94,English,,0,0,0,,but the bike still manages to absorb all these perturbations
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.60,0:06:06.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但单车依然能吸收这所有的扰动
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.94,0:06:08.88,English,,0,0,0,,and remain stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.94,0:06:08.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,保持平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:10.99,English,,0,0,0,,So, how does it do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.88,0:06:10.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是怎么做到的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.99,0:06:13.31,English,,0,0,0,,I think most people believe it's the wheels spinning
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.99,0:06:13.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大多数人会以为  是因为轮子的转动
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.31,0:06:15.81,English,,0,0,0,,that creates some sort of gyroscopic effect
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.31,0:06:15.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生了某种陀螺仪效应
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.81,0:06:17.92,English,,0,0,0,,that resists falling over
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.81,0:06:17.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使得它能抵抗倾倒
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.92,0:06:21.30,English,,0,0,0,,just like in this demonstration of gyroscopic precession.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.92,0:06:21.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就像陀螺仪进动效应的这个示意片段一样
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.30,0:06:22.53,English,,0,0,0,,The wheel stays upright
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.30,0:06:22.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,轮子会保持直立
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.53,0:06:25.34,English,,0,0,0,,even though gravity is pulling it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.53,0:06:25.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,克服了把它拉趴下来的重力
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.34,0:06:28.32,English,,0,0,0,,But this is not why bikes are stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.34,0:06:28.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这并非自行车能稳定的原因
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:29.29,English,,0,0,0,,Just watch what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:29.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,请看下例
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.29,0:06:31.39,English,,0,0,0,,when we lock the handlebars completely
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.29,0:06:31.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当车头方向完全锁死的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.39,0:06:33.43,English,,0,0,0,,so you can only go straight ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.39,0:06:33.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你只能笔直地往前走
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:34.88,English,,0,0,0,,- Locked out, locked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:34.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要锁了  要锁了
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:35.71,English,,0,0,0,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.88,0:06:35.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哇
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.57,0:06:40.20,English,,0,0,0,,- All that is happening is the steering is locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.57,0:06:40.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在我们只是锁住了转向机构
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.20,0:06:41.12,English,,0,0,0,,You just got to ride it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.20,0:06:41.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你只需要骑在上面
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:41.95,English,,0,0,0,,You don't have to turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.12,0:06:41.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不需要转弯
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,You just ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:43.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只需要骑
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:44.19,English,,0,0,0,,Letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.36,0:06:44.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,走起
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.19,0:06:46.40,English,,0,0,0,,- Some people tried going really fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.19,0:06:46.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些人尝试跑得非常快
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.20,0:06:55.80,English,,0,0,0,,Others experimented with extreme balancing techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.20,0:06:55.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其他人表现出精湛的平衡技巧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.80,0:06:57.50,English,,0,0,0,,- He's leaning. Don't go too fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.80,0:06:57.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要倒了  别跑太快
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.95,0:07:04.38,English,,0,0,0,,- But even with the gyroscopic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.38,0:07:05.53,English,,0,0,0,,effect of the wheels,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.95,0:07:05.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但即使车轮有陀螺仪效应
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.53,0:07:07.47,English,,0,0,0,,no one was able to keep the bike upright
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.47,0:07:09.07,English,,0,0,0,,for more than a few seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.53,0:07:09.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大家最多也只能让车子保持几秒钟不倒
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.54,0:07:13.37,English,,0,0,0,,- This is not safe for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.54,0:07:13.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一秒钟都稳不住
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.37,0:07:16.98,English,,0,0,0,,- It is just as hard to balance on a bike with locked steering
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.37,0:07:16.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在不能转向的自行车上保持平衡
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:19.00,English,,0,0,0,,as it is to balance on a stationary bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.98,0:07:19.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就跟立在静止的单车上一样难
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:21.27,English,,0,0,0,,- No, this one is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:21.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根本不可能啦
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:24.77,English,,0,0,0,,- Because you can't steer the bike back under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.27,0:07:24.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为你没法把车子的中心转到另一边
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.77,0:07:27.17,English,,0,0,0,,The real reason bicycles are stable without riders
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.77,0:07:27.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无人自行车能保持稳定的真正原因
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.17,0:07:31.42,English,,0,0,0,,is because they're cleverly designed to steer themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.17,0:07:31.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是因为其巧妙的设计  让车子能控制住自己
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.42,0:07:33.35,English,,0,0,0,,If they start falling to one side,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.42,0:07:33.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果车有迹象往某一边倒
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.35,0:07:35.68,English,,0,0,0,,the handlebars turn in that direction
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.35,0:07:35.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,车把就会往那边转
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:38.60,English,,0,0,0,,to steer the wheels back underneath them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:38.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,带着下面的轮子一起转过去
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:40.20,English,,0,0,0,,At least three mechanisms
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:40.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,至少有三种机制
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.20,0:07:43.14,English,,0,0,0,,are responsible for a bike's corrective steering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.20,0:07:43.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,共同对自行车的纠偏起作用
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.14,0:07:45.96,English,,0,0,0,,The first is that due to the angle of the front fork,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.14,0:07:45.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一点  由于前叉的这个角度
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.96,0:07:48.82,English,,0,0,0,,the steering axis intersects the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.96,0:07:48.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,转动轴与地面的交点
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:52.06,English,,0,0,0,,in front of where the wheel touches the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.82,0:07:52.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会落在轮子触地处的前方
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.06,0:07:54.05,English,,0,0,0,,So, if the bike starts leaning to the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.06,0:07:54.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此  当车子往左倾的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:55.78,English,,0,0,0,,the force from the ground on the tire
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:55.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地面对轮胎的力
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:58.33,English,,0,0,0,,turns the wheel to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.78,0:07:58.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会让前轮往左转
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.33,0:07:59.73,English,,0,0,0,,If the bike starts leaning right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.33,0:07:59.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而车子右倾的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.73,0:08:02.76,English,,0,0,0,,the force from the ground pushes the wheel to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.73,0:08:02.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地面对轮胎的力会推着前轮往右转
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.76,0:08:06.24,English,,0,0,0,,The front wheel of a bicycle is essentially a caster wheel,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.76,0:08:06.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自行车的前轮属于“脚轮”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:09.48,English,,0,0,0,,like those you find on strollers or shopping carts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.24,0:08:09.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,类似婴儿车、购物车下面的轮子
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.48,0:08:10.93,English,,0,0,0,,Whichever way you drive them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.48,0:08:10.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不管你往哪个方向前进
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.93,0:08:14.74,English,,0,0,0,,the wheel falls in line and rolls in the same direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.93,0:08:14.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,脚轮都始终跟你的前进方向保持一致
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.74,0:08:17.38,English,,0,0,0,,The second reason for a bike's corrective steering
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.74,0:08:17.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自行车纠偏的第二个机制
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.38,0:08:20.49,English,,0,0,0,,is that the center of mass of the handlebars and front wheel
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.38,0:08:20.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是车把和前轮的质心
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.49,0:08:23.81,English,,0,0,0,,are located slightly in front of the steering axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.49,0:08:23.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,略前于转动轴
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.81,0:08:25.58,English,,0,0,0,,So, when the bike leans left,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.81,0:08:25.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以  车子左倾时
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.58,0:08:28.24,English,,0,0,0,,their weight pushes the front wheel to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.58,0:08:28.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,车把和前轮的重量  会推着前轮往左转
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.24,0:08:31.20,English,,0,0,0,,If the bike leans right, their weight steers to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.24,0:08:31.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,若车子右倾  则会推着往右转
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.31,0:08:35.22,English,,0,0,0,,And the third mechanism is a gyroscopic effect
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.31,0:08:35.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第三个机制是“陀螺仪效应”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:38.04,English,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't keep the bike upright directly;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:38.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这不会直接对车子直立起作用
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.04,0:08:40.02,English,,0,0,0,,it just helps steer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.04,0:08:40.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这只是能辅助转向
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.02,0:08:41.18,English,,0,0,0,,If you have a gyroscope
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.02,0:08:41.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你有个陀螺仪
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.18,0:08:43.47,English,,0,0,0,,and you push down on the left-hand side,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.18,0:08:43.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,将其左端往下推
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.47,0:08:45.70,English,,0,0,0,,the gyro will turn left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.47,0:08:45.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,陀螺仪（的前端）会往左转
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.70,0:08:49.40,English,,0,0,0,,If you push down on the right side, it will turn right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.70,0:08:49.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,若从右端将其往下推 则会往右转
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.40,0:08:52.12,English,,0,0,0,,This is known as gyroscopic precession.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.40,0:08:52.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这被称为陀螺仪的“进动”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.12,0:08:54.17,English,,0,0,0,,It seems as though the force you apply
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.12,0:08:54.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看起来  你所施加的力
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.17,0:08:57.91,English,,0,0,0,,takes effect 90 degrees from where you applied it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.17,0:08:57.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所导致的运动  其方向与施力方向垂直
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.91,0:09:01.72,English,,0,0,0,,So, bikes are stable primarily because of steering.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.91,0:09:01.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此  自行车能稳定的主要原因是转向系统
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:05.30,English,,0,0,0,,They have built-in mechanisms for steering themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.72,0:09:05.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们有内在的机制来自己控制转向
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.30,0:09:07.81,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, you don't need all three mechanisms
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.30,0:09:07.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事实上  这三种机制即使没有全部做到
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:09.69,English,,0,0,0,,to create a stable bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:09.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,依然能搞出一辆稳定的自行车
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.69,0:09:12.52,English,,0,0,0,,Researchers created this weird-looking bicycle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.69,0:09:12.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,研究人员造了这台古怪的两轮车
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.52,0:09:13.88,English,,0,0,0,,to prove a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.52,0:09:13.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来证明这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.88,0:09:15.78,English,,0,0,0,,It has no gyroscopic effect
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.88,0:09:15.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它没有陀螺仪效应
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:17.70,English,,0,0,0,,thanks to counter-rotating wheels
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:17.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为有个逆向旋转的轮子
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:19.75,English,,0,0,0,,above the wheels that touch the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:19.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,处于接触地面的轮子之上
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.75,0:09:22.08,English,,0,0,0,,Plus, there is no caster effect
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.75,0:09:22.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它亦无脚轮的机制
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.92,English,,0,0,0,,because the front wheel touches the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:23.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为前轮与地面的接触位置
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.92,0:09:26.35,English,,0,0,0,,in front of the steering axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.92,0:09:26.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在转动轴的前面
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.35,0:09:30.08,English,,0,0,0,,But this bike is made stable by its mass distribution,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.35,0:09:30.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这车子可以靠其质量分布来维持稳定
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.08,0:09:31.61,English,,0,0,0,,the force of gravity on which
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.61,0:09:34.43,English,,0,0,0,,steers it in the direction of any lean.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.08,0:09:34.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其上的重力就会使它 转向它倾斜的方向
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.35,0:09:37.34,English,,0,0,0,,Understanding how bicycles work
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.35,0:09:37.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自行车维持平衡的原理
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:40.08,English,,0,0,0,,is still an active area of research.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.34,0:09:40.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仍处于活跃的研究中
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.08,0:09:42.10,English,,0,0,0,,There is a program you can use to input
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.10,0:09:43.77,English,,0,0,0,,all the different bicycle parameters
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.08,0:09:43.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个程序可以输入自行车的各式参数
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:47.65,English,,0,0,0,,and see the range of speeds over which it is self-stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:47.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来模拟自行车在何种速度下能自己保持稳定
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.65,0:09:50.58,English,,0,0,0,,{\an8}And this research is leading to better bikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.65,0:09:50.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an8}另一项研究旨在设计更优的自行车
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.93,0:09:53.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为了让骑行更安全  代尔夫特理工大学\N与自行车制造商  荷兰皇家自行车展开合作
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.26,0:09:56.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开发了一台可以智能辅助转向的原型自行车
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.58,0:09:53.30,English,,0,0,0,,{\an8}This prototype has a smart motor in the handlebars
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.58,0:09:53.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an8}这个原型车  在车把手下面有个智能马达
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:55.30,English,,0,0,0,,{\an8}to actively help steer,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.30,0:09:55.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an8}来主动帮助转向
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.30,0:09:58.00,English,,0,0,0,,{\an8}keeping the bike upright even at low speeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.30,0:09:58.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an8}让车子即使走得很慢  依然能保持直立
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:09:58.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,未来  这种电单车应能帮助减少事故
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.44,0:09:59.95,English,,0,0,0,,I guess it's fitting that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.44,0:09:59.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以说
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:02.63,English,,0,0,0,,we are still learning new things about bicycles
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.95,0:10:02.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,自行车还有很多奥秘等待我们去研究
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.63,0:10:04.76,English,,0,0,0,,since most of us are able to ride one
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.63,0:10:04.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大多数人尽管会骑车
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.76,0:10:08.93,English,,0,0,0,,without any knowledge of how we're actually doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.76,0:10:08.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,却完全不知道  自己为何能稳定地骑行
